When is it okay to not make the best move? When you know that the best move leads to a loss. He's going to trade the pawns on the queenside and have an outside passed pawn, and that's the game. Probably the best move is Kd7.
But if there's any hope for me, I've got to stir things up and cause some trouble. So, it's time to make a less than best move.
